                    <div id="addquest">
                        <div class="sectioninstructions"><p>The appeals process is strictly a <b>written process</b> - you will not be granted an in-person meeting with the Appeal Committee to further discuss this case or your appeal. Please explain the reason(s) which you believe justify your appeal. Since the appeal is not a re-hearing of the case, you should attach copies of any and all materials you feel are pertinent to the case. You must address each of the grounds for appeal that you check as specifically and comprehensively as possible. The information you provide and the case file provided by the Office of the Dean of Students will be used as the basis for all appeal action. <b>NOTE: Not agreeing with the hearing decision is not grounds for appeal.</b></p></div>                        <input type="hidden" name="numberOfAdditionalQuestions" value="5">

